description.text: Submodel containing techical data to the asset.
General information refers to the basic details about a product that would identify and describe it without getting into the detailed technical specifications.
The unique number assigned to the product.

The norm in fixed relation to the feature being described. This defines the parameters that influence the contents of the correlated feature. Type and number of the norm with issue year and issue month must be given, e.g. DIN ISO 4711:YYYY-MM.
The weight of the product.

A technical property generally refers to a characteristic or attribute that defines or describes the technical aspects of an object, system, material, or process. These properties are usually measurable or quantifiable and are critical in determining how something will function or perform in a specific context.
The unique code assigned to the manufacturer of the product.
The number of times the product can be used before it needs to be replaced.
The range of DC voltages that the product can operate within.
The nominal DC voltage that the product operates at.
The maximum current that the product can handle at a temperature of 40° C.
The ability of a product to withstand sudden increases in voltage.
Mechanical or electrical device for protection against polarity reversal of a voltage across a component
Cable length for data and energy transfer measured with connector
The characteristic of the cable, such as its suitability for energy chains.

Design, construction or function Assigned as more precise: electrical component, for the purpose of checking / determining the operability of (electrical) cables to a device (Note: electrical component which implements on the physical level a disconnectable connection between two lines and which usually has only a few contacts and is designed for rapid connection and disconnection |) / designation of the additional devices as a multi-contact test plug with connection cables.
minimum limit value for the bending radius of a cable or wire for stationary application/permanent installation
The level of protection against dust and water for the product, measured using the IP rating system.
The level of protection against dust and water for the product when used with the recommended connector.
